dialogue.introduction: Good morning. I'm Leberecht Maass. Lebe is fine, yep.
dialogue.library_intro: The German-born destroyer, the first genuine large-type. This shifted high temperature, high pressure engine, it could only have been designed in the country of technical skills! I'm not so great at open-sea warfare though... I'll do my best!
dialogue.secretary1: Nn, what is it? My boiler needs servicing...
dialogue.secretary3: Admiral, what is it? Is this one of this country's greetings? It's going to be difficult until I'm used to it.
dialogue.secretaryidle: Ah, It's not that I'm bored, I'm just fine, yep.
dialogue.secretarymarried: Admiral, you're always working so hard, aren't you. But, you shouldn't push yourself so much. I'll work with you.
dialogue.wedding: Admiral, why the serious face? Eh? What's this box... O-oh. Thank you.
dialogue.show_players_score: Looking at the report? Analysis is important.
dialogue.docking_minor_damage: Ah, they got me. I've gotta get fixed.
dialogue.docking_complete: Admiral, a comrade's repairs have been completed.
dialogue.ship_construction: Admiral, looks like a new comrade is here.
dialogue.start_a_sortie: Not commerce raiding, but a fleet battle?... I- I can do it!
dialogue.battle_start: Fleet battle, huh... Okay, here I go!
dialogue.night_battle: Night battle huh, I'll give it a shot
dialogue.mvp: I did the best? Oh... that's great, yep.
dialogue.moderately_damaged: The engine room is alright, I can still sail forth.
dialogue.sunk: I'm sinking, once again, huh. But, this time... it was in a real battle...

hourly.0000: Midnight. It's a new day, yeah?
hourly.0200: 2 o'clock. I wonder if Max is still going?
hourly.0300: 3 o'clock. Ngh... Admiral, aren't you tired? Wow, that's impressive.
hourly.0500: 5 o'clock. It's morning, some new missions have come.
hourly.0600: Good morning. 6 o'clock. Admiral, good day to you.
hourly.0700: 7 o'clock. Breakfast time, yeah? I'll go and get it started.
hourly.0800: 8 o'clock. Admiral, how's the NÃ¼rnberger Rostbratwurst? Was it tasty?
hourly.0900: 9 o'clock. Almost time for serious action, yeah?
hourly.1000: 10 o'clock. About time to sortie. But, I've gotta be careful of mines.
hourly.1100: 11 o'clock. I won't confuse fishing boats and enemy vessels, yep. Naturally.
hourly.1200: 12 o'clock. Lunch time. What would be good for lunch, Admiral?
hourly.1300: It's 13 o'clock. I wonder if Max is okay, I'm a bit worried.
hourly.1400: It's 14 o'clock. Practice is important, even in the North Sea, yep.
hourly.1500: 15 o'clock. Talking about seaworthiness...nah, I'm just wondering...
hourly.1600: 16 o'clock. It's okay, I can do it.
hourly.1700: 17 o'clock. It's getting a little dark, yep.
hourly.1800: 18 o'clock. What shall we do for dinner?
hourly.1900: The Sauerkraut and Eisbein, how is it? Admiral, is it tasty? Ah, 19 o'clock.
hourly.2100: 21 o'clock. About time for night battles, yeah? I'm not so great at those.
hourly.2200: 22 o'clock. It's amazing, everybody here just loves night battles, I'm surprised.
hourly.2300: 23 o'clock. Admiral, thanks for everything today. Let's do our best tomorrow too!
